1. made an app using steps from the express workshop
2. installed sequelize: npm install sequelize pg@"^6.4.2" --save
3. created our db in the terminal:  createdb wikistack
4. added a new module called "models". within models added a new index.js for our sequelize initation code
5. required sequelize and connected it to "the currently running db process" within models/index.js
6. defined our models in models/index.js and module exported them
7. required our models in app.js and subsequently synced our models before the server calls its .listen method with a port
